5	12	["QR Code Generation", "Self-service kiosk interface", "Automated SMS Notification", "Real-time inventory tracking", "Statistical Report Generation"]	3. Library management system using QR codes for book borrowing and returns\r\nAbstract: > Traditional academic libraries continue to struggle with process inefficiencies caused by manual book logging, outdated barcode scanners, and paper-based attendance tracking. These archaic methods frequently result in inaccurate inventory data, lost materials, and extended transaction times for students. This research study introduces a modernized, web-based Library Management System (LMS) that deeply integrates QR code technology to automate and streamline core library operations. The proposed system generates unique, scannable QR codes for both individual library materials and student identification cards, enabling a highly efficient self-service kiosk for borrowing and returning books. Additionally, the platform features automated overdue SMS notifications, a real-time inventory tracking dashboard for librarians, and automated statistical report generation. Built using a robust PHP and MySQL architecture, the system aims to significantly reduce the administrative workload on library staff. The project will be executed using the Rapid Application Development (RAD) approach. Evaluation of the system will be conducted through comprehensive user testing focusing on transaction speed, accuracy, and overall user acceptance to ensure it provides a superior alternative to manual library management.	ALL	0.60	10|0.8660,14|0.7427,58|0.6660,57|0.6474,3|0.6236	\N	[{"feature": "QR Code Generation", "User Abstract": {"present": true, "evidence": null}, "Abstract 1": {"present": true, "evidence": "QR-based attendance tracking"}, "Abstract 2": {"present": true, "evidence": "QR code scanning"}, "Abstract 3": {"present": true, "evidence": "QR code verification"}, "Abstract 4": {"present": false, "evidence": null}, "Abstract 5": {"present": f