6	12	["QR Code Scanning", "Report Management"]	The Library Management System (LMS) was developed to address inefficiencies in the traditional, manual operations of the Iloilo Science and Technology University (ISAT U) library, where attendance and book tracking were prone to delays, inaccuracies, and human error. Recognizing the need to modernize these processes, this study aimed to design and develop a web-based LMS that integrates QR code technology to streamline attendance monitoring, manage borrowing and returning transactions, and generate data-driven reports to support decision-making for future book acquisitions. The system was developed using a throwaway prototyping model, ensuring continuous feedback from users including librarians, faculty, and students throughout the design, implementation, and testing phases. Key functionalities include real-time QR-based attendance tracking, categorization of library materials, book reservation and status updates, damage reporting, and the generation of statistical and operational reports. The system’s performance was rigorously evaluated following the ISO 25010 software quality model, focusing on functional suitability, usability, performance efficiency, reliability, security, maintainability, and portability. The results showed the LMS achieved a “Very Good” overall rating (M=4.12), performing particularly in functional completeness, efficiency, and usability, while noting areas for improvement in portability. These outcomes highlight the system’s capacity to enhance library operations, reduce manual workload, and improve user satisfaction. Thus, this study provides valuable implications for academic libraries seeking to integrate modern technologies, demonstrating how digital systems can strengthen library management, support strategic resource planning, and elevate the overall user experience.	ALL	0.60	10|1.0000,57|0.7877,14|0.7081,62|0.6526,6|0.6404,58|0.6346,26|0.6108	\N	[{"feature": "QR Code Scanning", "User Abst