7	12	["Live Location Monitoring", "Arrival-time predictions", "Passenger location-pinning"]	Urban commuters frequently experience significant stress and wasted time due to the unpredictability of public transportation schedules and the lack of real-time transit visibility. This study aims to address these challenges by designing and developing "TransitTrack," a mobile application integrated with real-time GPS tracking specifically for daily commuters utilizing local buses and modernized jeepneys. The proposed system features live location monitoring of transit vehicles, algorithmic estimated time of arrival (ETA) predictions, and a passenger location-pinning module to alert drivers of waiting commuters. Developed using the React Native framework for cross-platform mobile compatibility and a Node.js backend, the application seeks to optimize daily travel schedules and reduce wait times at transit stops. The project will utilize the Agile Software Development Model to ensure iterative improvements based on commuter feedback. Finally, system usability, reliability, and user satisfaction will be evaluated using the Technology Acceptance Model (TAM), utilizing a Likert-scale survey distributed to local university students and daily wage workers to determine its effectiveness in easing traffic congestion and commuter anxiety.	ALL	0.60	17|0.7825,2|0.7352,8|0.6232	\N	[{"feature": "Live Location Monitoring", "User Abstract": {"present": true, "evidence": null}, "Abstract 1": {"present": true, "evidence": "Real-time jeepney tracking"}, "Abstract 2": {"present": false, "evidence": null}, "Abstract 3": {"present": true, "evidence": "GPS real-time tracking"}}, {"feature": "Arrival-time predictions", "User Abstract": {"present": true, "evidence": null}, "Abstract 1": {"present": false, "evidence": null}, "Abstract 2": {"present": false, "evidence": null}, "Abstract 3": {"present": false, "evidence": null}}, {"feature": "Passenger location-pinning", "User Abstract": {"present": tr